

r.info - 

r.info reports some basic information about a user-specified @glossary("raster",16.glossary/rastdata.def)
@glossary("map layer",16.glossary/maplayer.def).  This map layer must exist the user's current @glossary("mapset",16.glossary/mapset.def)
search path.  Information about the map's boundaries, @glossary("resolution",16.glossary/res.def),
@glossary("projection",16.glossary/projtn.def), data type, @glossary("category",16.glossary/cat.def) number, database location and
mapset, and history are put into a table and written to standard
output.  The types of information listed can also be found in the
"cats", "cellhd", and "hist" directories under the mapset in
which the named map is stored.

